<p><tags><tag kind="heading2">## </tag></tags>External Folders</p>
<p></p>
<p>In External Folders, you can edit classic text and markdown files from anywhere on your Mac. As an example, you can point Ulysses to a folder on Dropbox, and have its contents behave just like native groups and sheets. Make sure that “External Folders” are enabled in preferences, then add one via the <element kind="code" startTag="`">+</element> button in the respective section header of the library.</p>
<p></p>
<p>Some features will be limited for external folders (no images, no attachments). Writing, however, will still be great. And this is what counts after all, isn’t it?</p>
<p></p>
<p><tags><tag kind="divider">----</tag></tags></p>
